To run .Rmd file:

Download and install R (version >= 3.6.1)
Download and install RStudio (version >= 1.3)
Open the file with RStudio
Click on Knit in the top left pane.
Follow any prompts to install a number of packages.

You may need to click on Knit again after installing all packages.

The output is an HTML file, viewable in a browser, that reproduces
graphics in the paper and more. As a side effect, it also rewrites the
graphics in the ../figs directory of your local git clone.

